FBIS4-63465 "drsov099_e_94012" FBIS-SOV-94-099 Daily Report 20 May 1994 UKRAINE International Affairs Rukh Urges Leaders To Halt Withdrawal of Nuclear Weapons Rukh Urges Leaders To Halt Withdrawal of Nuclear Weapons LD2105092194 Kiev Radio Ukraine World Service in Ukrainian 2200 GMT 20 May 94 LD2105092194 Kiev Radio Ukraine World Service Ukrainian BFN [Text] The People's Movement of Ukraine [Rukh] has issued an appeal calling on the Ukrainian president and Supreme Council to take effective measures for the Constitution and laws of Ukraine to be implemented in Crimea and the territorial integrity of the Ukrainian state to be ensured. Under the conditions of Russia's continuing informational, organizational, and parliamentary aggression in Crimea, the People's Movement deems it necessary to halt the withdrawal of nuclear weapons from the territory of Ukraine, the document stresses. Rukh also appeals to the UN Security Council and the Conference on Security and Cooperation in Europe and requests them to prevent Ukraine from being taken to pieces and being plunged into a civil war.
